f=Brand Studio/tempo/custom/sound-identity/SKILL.md · in=sound-identity fourth definer: what brand *sounds* like music mood ranges, tone, sonic do/don'ts written operator-approved sonic guide brand, consumed whenever video, podcast, audio content gets made. law atlas/lena/weave: written guide, sonic enforcement. brands doing audio content, tempo documented no-op folder exists, nothing runs. · p=Audio brand dimension teams improvise: video gets whatever track felt right day, tone drifts producer, nothing accumulates. brands video/audio matters (which increasingly means any brand pulse serializes TikTok/Reels/YouTube), sonic guide makes sound brand asset instead per-edit mood. · wu=Triggers: "video music," "sound [content]," "VO tone," "build our sonic guide" invoked pixel/pulse whenever produced content carries audio. · st:/ Protocol=`Load the brand's sonic guide (config path) \· -> If none: BUILD with the operator (template; derived from the brand kit's mood + \· voice guide's register + real reference tracks the operator approves) \· -> Select for the content: mood range match + licensed-registry-only (usage-licensing \· skill governs what "licensed" means)` · in=**Build (once brand):** derive what exists atlas's kit mood, lena's register plain-spoken brand doesn't get cinematic bombast), weave's arc emotional range plus operator-approved reference tracks. Encode template's testable statements ("energetic never frantic; acoustic over synthetic; VO: warm, unhurried, announcer voice"). Operator sign-off freezes v1. **Select (per content):** match content's chapter/mood guide's ranges; choose **only licensed registry** (usage-licensing's ledger); document selection output. need outside registry license request path, never "grab hope." **Maintain:** selections log; repeated off-guide requests guide review (amendment, operator-owned); guide versioned like definer document. · of=selection: `[content] [track/registry-ID] guide-fit: [range matched] license: [registry ref]`. Guide build/amendments follow template. · pr=**No guide, sonic enforcement; registry entry, track.**, **Derived definers** sound never contradicts voice, kit, arc., **License before use, cost before commitment.**, **Dormant state**: no-audio brands get explicit no-op, structure intact. · f=guide urgent content neutral selection labeled "no sonic guide," build loop starts., registry usage-licensing's acquisition path runs first; nothing unlicensed ships. · b:with Other Skills=`usage-licensing` (sibling) owns what legally used; skill owns what *fits*., **pixel** produces content scores; **pulse's** platform playbooks note per-platform audio norms; **spark's** gate covers audio coherence once guide exists fifth reference, noted dormant-until-built coherence-qa's spirit).